Notes: The 'row_id' is a unique identifier for the CSV row itself, which corresponds to the instance of the main entity DrugPrescription. It does not map to a deeper property but identifies the main entity instance.
The patient_id corresponds to the patient associated with the drug prescription. The path to Patient entity via 'hasPatient' is the most semantically appropriate to represent this linkage.

The medication ATC code is best represented as a code of the Drug entity linked to the DrugPrescription. Since the code is a property of the drug, the two-hop path through 'hasDrug' then 'hasCode' is more semantically accurate than directly attaching the code to the prescription.

Diagnosis code corresponds to the indication to start the drug prescription; the 'hasIndicationToStart' property linking to Diagnosis is the best semantic fit. Although 'hasIndicationToStart' can link to Intent, diagnosis is more appropriate for a diagnosis code.
'creation_date' fits naturally to the 'hasDateTime' property of the DrugPrescription to record when the prescription was created.
'times_a_day' denotes frequency of administration, best mapped to 'hasFrequency' property, which points to a Quantity entity representing frequency.
'dosage' corresponds to the quantity of drug prescribed, thus maps best to 'hasDrugQuantity' property linking to a Quantity entity. This is more specific than the general 'hasQuantity' property.
